  "detailedContent": {
    "mythology": "Tefnut'smythologycenters on her role as a primordial creative force and the essential moisture needed for existence. As one of the first beings to emerge from the creator god, she represents the fundamental principle of water in the atmosphere. In the Heliopolitan creation myth, the self-created godAtumemerged from the primordial waters ofNuand created the first divine pair:Shu(air) and Tefnut (moisture). Some accounts describeAtumspitting or sneezing them into existence, while others describe an act of self-generation. Together,Shuand Tefnut represent the fundamental atmospheric conditions—air and moisture—necessary for life. They then producedGeb(earth) andNut(sky), continuing the cosmic generation."
  },
